    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-19T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="439"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.4016/42: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-19T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 19, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 20—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>719. Embassy’s telegram No. 708, June 16, 8 p.m. The Embassy and Consulates in
                    unoccupied France are receiving inquiries from American Jews as to whether or
                    not they should register as Jews before July 14 under the recent anti-Semitic
                    laws.</p>
                <p>Article 2 of the Enabling Act carries penalties of fines up to 10,000 francs and
                    imprisonment in Leipzig as much as 1 year or both for those who fail to comply,
                    adding significantly “these provisions not to affect the right of the prefect to
                    order internment in a special camp, even if the delinquent is French.”</p>
                <p>The Embassy would much appreciate an early expression of the Department’s views
                    in order to give appropriate advice to American residents of Jewish
                    extraction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
